# Frontend Stack & Patterns

## Stack
- Next.js 16+ (App Router, `proxy.ts`, `"use cache"`, async request APIs)
- React 19+ (Server Components default, `"use client"` pushed to leaf nodes)
- Tailwind CSS v4+ (CSS-first config via `@theme`, `@import "tailwindcss"`, built-in container queries)
- shadcn/ui v4 (use shadcn/skills for component context; supports both Radix and Base UI primitives)

## 1. File Structure
- Components live in `components/` at project root, organized by domain:
  - `components/ui/` — shadcn primitives. Never modify directly; extend via `className` + `cn()`.
  - `components/{domain}/` — composite components (e.g., `components/product/product-card.tsx`).
  - `components/layout/` — site-wide layout (header, footer, sidebar).
  - `components/sections/` — page section compositions.
  - `components/animations/` — animation wrappers (ScrollReveal, etc.).
- Never create `components/` folders inside `app/` route directories.
- Page-specific markup stays in the page file; extract to a named component only when reused.
- Add new shadcn components with `npx shadcn@latest add <name>` — never copy-paste from docs.

## 2. Server vs Client Components
- Default to Server Components — no directive needed.
- Add `"use client"` only for: event handlers, React hooks, browser APIs, or context consumers.
- Push `"use client"` to the smallest possible leaf component.
- Fetch data in Server Components via `async` / `await` — never `useEffect` + `fetch` for initial data.
- All request APIs are async: `await cookies()`, `await headers()`, `await params`, `await searchParams`.
- Use `proxy.ts` (not `middleware.ts`) for request interception in Next.js 16+.

## 3. Layout & Responsiveness
**Mobile-first always.** Base (unprefixed) Tailwind classes target the smallest screen. Scale up with ascending breakpoints (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`).

**Two-tier responsive strategy:**
- **Page-level (macro):** Viewport media queries (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`) for grid column counts, page padding, and section spacing.
- **Component-level (micro):** Container queries (`@container` on parent, `@sm:` / `@md:` / `@lg:` on children) for internal padding, text sizing, aspect ratios, and layout direction within reusable components.

**Reusable components must use container queries** for internal responsiveness. See `docs/internal/LayoutSystem.md` for full syntax reference and grid patterns.

Card grids in catalog / e-commerce contexts: **minimum 2 columns on mobile** (`grid-cols-2`). Scale with `md:grid-cols-3` or `lg:grid-cols-4`. Never single-column for product/card grids.

Page padding scales down on mobile: `px-4 sm:px-6` not `px-6`. `py-8 sm:py-12 lg:py-16` not `py-16`.

## 4. Images
- Every `next/image` with `fill` must have a `sizes` prop.
- Grid cards: `sizes="(max-width: 640px) 50vw, (max-width: 1024px) 33vw, 25vw"`
- Hero / full-width: `sizes="100vw"`
- Image containers use `aspect-[ratio]` with container-query override: `aspect-[3/4] @sm:aspect-[4/5]`.
- Set meaningful `alt` text — empty string only for purely decorative images.
- Use `priority` only on above-the-fold hero images.

## 5. Design Tokens
- All tokens as CSS variables in `globals.css` via `:root` and Tailwind `@theme`.
- Never hardcode hex/rgb colors — use semantic tokens (`bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`).
- Brand-specific colors use a project namespace in theme config (e.g., `trunk-*`, `brand-*`).
- Typography uses `font-serif` / `font-sans` CSS variable families.
- Refer to `docs/internal/DesignSystem.md` for project-specific token values when available.

## 6. Animations
- GSAP for scroll-triggered animations, complex timelines, and physics-based motion.
- Framer Motion for layout animations, presence/exit, and simple transitions.
- Always clean up GSAP instances in `useEffect` / `useLayoutEffect` cleanup. Prefer `useGSAP()` from `@gsap/react`.
- Apply `transform-gpu` on animated elements for hardware acceleration.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` — provide a static fallback or disable animations.
- Animation wrapper components go in `components/animations/`.

## 7. Existing Project Safety
When working in an established codebase (live production site):
- Do not rewrite working components to adopt new patterns unless explicitly asked.
- Migrate incrementally: adopt container queries in new or modified components; leave stable ones alone.
- shadcn Base UI migration is component-by-component. Use `npx shadcn@latest add <name> --diff` to preview changes before applying. Radix-based components continue to work — only migrate when touching that component.
- Test at 390px, 768px, and 1280px after any layout change. Verify visually, not just via build passing.
- When fixing responsiveness in existing components, match the codebase's existing token usage and naming patterns.

## 8. Anti-patterns — never do these
- Desktop-first breakpoints (`text-xl md:text-base`) — always mobile-first.
- Viewport queries (`sm:`, `md:`) for internal component layout — use container queries.
- Omitting `sizes` on `next/image` with `fill`.
- `aspect-[4/5]` without a mobile-appropriate container-query override.
- Creating new primitive UI components (buttons, inputs, dialogs) — use shadcn/ui.
- Placing component files inside `app/` route directories — they go in `components/`.
- `useEffect` + `fetch` for data fetchable in Server Components.
- `any` in TypeScript — use proper types or `unknown`.
- `next/router` — use `next/navigation`.
- `middleware.ts` — use `proxy.ts` (Next.js 16+).
- Hardcoding color values — use design tokens.
- String concatenation for `className` — use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils`.